<div class="comments" style="padding: 0px 20px 10px 0px;">Posted by: <a href="http://www.archinect.com/members/profile_view_ind.php?id=13458">Orhan Ayyce</a> on Jan 10, 07 | 8:56 am</div>

</div><div style="padding: 10px 0px 10px 0px; border-bottom: 1px dashed #C7C2BE;">

<div class="comments" style="padding: 0px 20px 5px 0px;">super interesting article!  so many potential tangents! <br />
<br />
although it may not be a substitute for RL (jump), the characteristics of the SL environment (when left to the average individual) are astonishingly banal, which does, unfortunately, reflect RL...  and with this reinforcement comes, at least in part, +q's concern.  boring gives birth to boring, propagates boring, more boring...<br />
<br />
